This paper is primarily focused on the learning of activation functions in deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the Lipschitz constant of neural networks, which is a topic related to optimization and numerical analysis, making cs.NE (Numerical Analysis) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks in computer vision applications, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible sub-category. The paper's focus on controlling the Lipschitz constant of neural networks is also related to the topic of regularization, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of variational methods suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Systems and Control).
